RED WINES

POMMARD EPENOTS 1953 Estate Bottled, L. Poirier

One of the best examples of Pommard produced during this decade.

CLOS DE LA ROCHE 1952 Estate Bottled, Jacques

Some of the greatest wines of Burgundy are produced in the township of Morey from whence comes this remark- able Clos de la Roche. Sturdy, full — a big wine.

BEAUNE GREVES 1949 Estate Bottled, Duvault-Blochet

Authentic 1949s have almost disappeared completely. Here is an extraordinarily fine survivor.

WHITE WINES

CORTON CHARLEMAGNE 1955 Estate Bottled, Chapuis

The white wines from the Corton Charlemagne vineyard are among the noblest of France, hard to come by, and can be classed with the great Montrachets.

MEURSAULT, CLOS DES PERRIERES 1955, Estate Bottled, Grivault

Many authorities consider Clos des Perrieres (43 acres ) the best single vineyard of Meursault. A consistent favorite among fanciers of white Burgundies.

RHINE & MOSELLE WINES

GRAACHER HIMMELREICH SPAT- LESE 1955, Estate Bottled, Pfarrkirche

The vineyard is owned by the Church of St. Michael on the Moselle and the proceeds thereof go towards support- ing the Church. The devotion to the care of the vine and the celler is reflected in the outstanding quality shown by this truly magnificent Moselle.

SCHLOSS VOLLRADS CABINET 1953 Estate Bottled, Graf Matuschka-Greiffenclau

In great years, the wines of Schloss Vollrads are among the greatest of Germany. The title “‘Cabinet”’ is not given lightly here — it means the best of class and extraordinary wine of great distinction.

A distinguished example of Estate bottled Cote de Beaune.

BEAUNE, CLOS DES MOUCHES 1953 Estate Bottled, Duvault-Blochet

The Clos des Mouches vineyard is directly adjacent to the boundary of Pommard and produces a distinguished red

WHITE WINES

MEURSAULT CHARMES 1953 Estate Bottled, Joseph Matrot

One of the pleasantest Meursaults we have run across.

CHABLIS VAUDESIR 1955 Estate Bottled, Louis Begue

Perhaps the most famous of the 8 Grand Cru vineyards of Chablis is that of Vaudesir. Here is a perfect expression produced during an outstanding year. Unfortunately, all we could acquire were 30 cases.

RHINE & PFALZ WINES

RUDESHEIMER ROTTLAND SPATLESE 1953, Estate Bottled, Staatsweingut

A glorious 1953. Only 20 irreplaceable cases remain.

FORSTER JESUITENGARTEN 1955, Estate Bottled, Bassermann-Jordan

The Jesuitengarten vineyard of the Pfalz is rated as the most valuable agricultural land in Germany. A rare wine with great elegance.

A few of the wines of the Rhone Valley, such as Chateauneuf-du- Pape and Tavel, need no introduction. But there are many others, red, rosé and white, which are less celebrated, but nevertheless won- derful for everyday drinking. After tasting over a hundred such wines, we have selected three, bottled

in Avignon, and we are calling them PONT D’AVIGNON, in honor of the old broken bridge and the old roundelay. They are just glorified ‘vins du pays, but delightful ones; a dry white wine, pale and clean: a soft, full- bodied, well-balanced red; a fragrant little rosé, fresh and gay and charming.
